task.summary: - bug in open versionDir function. it always opened current.
- print warning when a corrupted propertyNode.xml file was found
- job execution behaviour not as expected: /path/to/ + exec is not equal to /path/to/exec in deadline o_O - job submission window has a new field with the according renderer help command
- context menu cleanup and fix for text - delete dialog updated
- live dir was not being removed when output was deleted. fixed
- outputs now with cleanup function: remove all versions except current and live
- mp3 player now with support to choose which track to play
- vlc.py now access payload vlc. vlc doesn't have to be installed anymore - variable fix for the audio player
- output cleanup bug fixed (if there was an exclusion) - context menu reworked - open asset/shot preparation
- asset/shot loaders can now directly open the corresponding asset/shot
- screen casts added and removed to screenCastsList by signals - cleanUpNode function added - double click on LDR now opens containing tree
- removed some print statements - pigz (2.3) and tar (bsdtar 2.8.3 - libarchive 2.8.3) added to payload for future multithreaded project gzip archiving and extraction

- pypelyne configuration now in separate file - djv integrated into payload as default sequence viewer - if rv is installed, rv is used. otherwise djv - fix for deadline slave launcher: env vars were not available. now there is a launcher script in src/tool_integration/thinkbox_deadline - maya computeAbsolutePaths now converts to workspace relative paths - maya computeAbsolutePaths now also considers cacheFile nodes and aiImage nodes
- wrong logic for choosing the sequence viewer
- now with maya workspace.mel template (needed for proper check out)
- nodeWidget separate file - playerWidget separate file - server/client preparation
- code cleanup - code simplification - extended options
- asset-saver or shot-saver with all connections can now be exported to the library - adding library loader functionality
- small approval functionality fix in contextMenu
